# Keep .local/bin out of stow's sibling-tree analysis. The sway package
# canonically owns .local/bin/start-sway (the session launcher), but the
# scripts package has pre-existing absolute-symlink entries (claude,
# python3.11 → ~/.local/share/...) that stow globally rejects. Pulling
# those into the same tree aborts stow for sway, so we manage
# start-sway via a direct ln -s in bootstrap instead.
\.local
